{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17644864","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17644864"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:09:06+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:09:06+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18069"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18069","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18069"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.1,0.05,0,0.86,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10783"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76024"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10783","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10783"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18069"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61525"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"2982"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5656"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25137"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25979"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76024","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76024"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ESeclusion is a restrictive intervention sometimes used in mental health settings to manage acute behavioural disturbance that poses an immediate risk of serious harm.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a key requirement for implementing seclusion?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Hourly observations","Use as a first-line behavioural management strategy","Continuation until behaviour completely normalises","Use only after less restrictive options have failed","Implementation without medical review"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct requirement is that seclusion must be used \u003Cstrong\u003Eonly after less restrictive options have failed\u003C/strong\u003E. This reflects the principle of using the least restrictive intervention necessary to ensure safety.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHourly observations\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because seclusion requires continuous monitoring of the patient to ensure their safety and wellbeing.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUse as a first-line behavioural management strategy\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because less restrictive interventions such as de-escalation techniques must be attempted first.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EContinuation until behaviour completely normalises\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because seclusion should be terminated as soon as the immediate risk of serious harm has passed.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImplementation without medical review\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because medical assessment and authorisation are mandatory both before and during the period of seclusion.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESeclusion represents a significant restriction on a person\u0027s liberty and must only be implemented with appropriate safeguards, documentation, and oversight. The focus should always be on using the least restrictive option necessary to maintain safety.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Seclusion is the supervised confinement of a person alone in a room from which they cannot freely exit.","Seclusion can only be used as a last resort when less restrictive interventions have failed.","Seclusion requires continuous monitoring and regular medical review to ensure patient safety."],"references":["Mental Health Act 2016. Queensland Health. Updated 2021. https://www.health.qld.gov.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0025/465163/cpp-seclusion.pdf"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61525"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18069"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61525","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61525"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-01T22:29:36+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-01T22:32:15+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10783"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76024"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/10"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udfad","name":"Psychiatry","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior"